.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="159" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="159" type="mainText">Worker. - Length lines. Head black: the antennae, mandibles, and the anterior margin of the face, rufo-testaceous; the thorax, abdomen and legs pale rufo-testaceous: the first node of the abdomen subtriangular, the upper margin being curved, the curve channelled from the base to the apex, the latter emarginate; the second node globose; the sides of the abdomen compressed, but not strangulated in the middle.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="159" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="159" type="mainText">This species was captured by Mr. Bates, at Santarem, Brazil; it was found coursing over herbage, and also on sandy banks. In mv own Collection.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="159" type="mainText">*</paragraph>
